<subSubSection id="DCF9AAB63E3C4F0DFCA73D74FE1BFC6D" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="945CF93D3E3C4F0CFCA73D74FB4DFD66" blockId="8.[807,1423,302,692]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFCA73D74FC2AFE96" box="[807,926,303,324]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Frons narrow. Supra-antennal setae absent. Fore femur with posterodorsal seta near apex. Apical tarsomere of fore leg lacking claws in male. Hind femur with erect dorsal setae. Mid and hind tibia with irregular, sinuous rows of enlarged setulae anterodorsally. Tergites and often thorax of most species with silver pollinosity. Female abdominal segment 7 completely sclerotized, forming a parasitic 
<typeStatus id="4B58479F3E3C4F0CFAAB3E5EFAE8FDC8" box="[1323,1372,517,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
ovipositor. Intersegment 7–8 modified, with sclerotization of various forms. Posterior segments (9–10) of female abdomen form a sharp, pointed, piercing stylet. Male with subepandrial plate with long, posterolateral lobes; aedeagus extremely elongate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="945CF93D3E3C4F0CFCA73E97FBB4FC6A" blockId="8.[807,1423,716,1903]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFCA73E97FC6AFD33" box="[807,990,716,737]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Natural history</emphasis>
. Species of 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFBE43E97FB5CFD33" authorityName="Brues" authorityYear="1904" box="[1124,1256,716,737]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFBE43E97FB5CFD33" box="[1124,1256,716,737]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Melaloncha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are endoparasitoids of a variety of bees, but most records are of attacks on stingless bees (Meliponini: Apinae: 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFAB83F52FA3FFCCD" box="[1336,1419,777,799]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Apidae</taxonomicName>
; summarized by 
<bibRefCitation id="F07284CC3E3C4F0CFC5E3F73FBC5FCEC" author="Disney RHL" box="[990,1137,808,830]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref31024" refString="Disney RHL. 1994. Scuttle flies: the Phoridae. London: Chapman &amp; Hall." type="book" year="1994">Disney, 1994</bibRefCitation>
). There is one record of a parasitized 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFC343F1CFB4BFC8E" authority="Cresson" authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1879" box="[948,1279,839,860]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFC343F1CFB22FC8E" box="[948,1174,839,860]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bombus mexicanus</emphasis>
Cresson
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFA943F1CFA3FFC8F" baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[1300,1419,839,861]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Bombinae">Bombinae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFCA73F3EFCCDFCA9" box="[807,889,869,891]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Apidae</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F07284CC3E3C4F0CFC033F3EFB9CFCAE" author="Ramirez W" box="[899,1064,869,892]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="177" refId="ref31369" refString="Ramirez W. 1982. Bombus mexicanus Cresson, un hospedante de Melaloncha, moscas parasitas de la abeja de miel en el nuevo mundo. Revista de Biologia Tropical 30: 177." type="journal article" year="1982">Ramirez, 1982</bibRefCitation>
) but unfortunately the fly specimen has been lost (P. Hanson, University of 
<collectingCountry id="ECF4B9AD3E3C4F0CFACD3FDFFCEFFC6B" name="Costa Rica" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="945CF93D3E3C4F0CFCC03F99FB1FFB39" blockId="8.[807,1423,716,1903]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
One species, 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFC513F99FB0BFC05" authority="Borgmeier" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1935" box="[977,1215,961,983]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ronnai">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFC513F99FBF5FC05" box="[977,1089,962,983]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. ronnai</emphasis>
Borgmeier
</taxonomicName>
(see species treatment, below), is a well-known parasitoid of introduced honey bees, 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFC323FA4FBE6FBC6" box="[946,1106,1023,1044]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Apis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellifera">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFC323FA4FBE6FBC6" box="[946,1106,1023,1044]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Apis mellifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (Apinae, 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFB5E3FA4FA85FBC7" box="[1246,1329,1023,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Apidae</taxonomicName>
), but its native host is not known. Other species of 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFA8B3846FA3BFBE0" authorityName="Brues" authorityYear="1904" box="[1291,1423,1053,1074]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFA8B3846FA3BFBE0" box="[1291,1423,1053,1074]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Melaloncha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will occasionally attack honey bees attracted to honeysprayed undergrowth (B. V. Brown, pers. observ.). A citation of up to eight species of 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFB353822FA8DFB5C" authorityName="Brues" authorityYear="1904" box="[1205,1337,1145,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFB353822FA8DFB5C" box="[1205,1337,1145,1166]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Melaloncha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reared from honey bees in 
<collectingCountry id="ECF4B9AD3E3C4F0CFBA138C3FB16FB7C" box="[1057,1186,1176,1198]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F07284CC3E3C4F0CFB3838C3FAD2FB7C" author="Ramirez W" box="[1208,1382,1176,1198]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="25 - 28" refId="ref31403" refString="Ramirez W. 1984. Biologia del genero Melaloncha (Phoridae), moscas parasitoides de la abeja domestica (Apis mellifera L.) en Costa Rica. Revista de Biologia Tropical 32: 25 - 28." type="journal article" year="1984">Ramírez, 1984</bibRefCitation>
) is unsubstantiated; all voucher specimens I received from Dr Ramirez were 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFBB4388DFB10FB39" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1935" box="[1076,1188,1238,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ronnai">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFBB4388DFB10FB39" box="[1076,1188,1238,1259]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. ronnai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="945CF93D3E3C4F0CFCC038AFFB93FA71" blockId="8.[807,1423,716,1903]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
A record of a 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFC6C38AFFB79FAD8" box="[1004,1229,1268,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFC6C38AFFBC4FADB" box="[1004,1136,1268,1289]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Melaloncha</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
reared from an anthophorid bee (quoted in 
<bibRefCitation id="F07284CC3E3C4F0CFBF53948FAA4FAFB" author="Roubik DW" box="[1141,1296,1299,1321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref31524" refString="Roubik DW. 1989. Ecology and natural history of tropical bees. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press." type="book" year="1989">Roubik, 1989</bibRefCitation>
) is unconfirmed, and based on the similarity of the pupae with the described pupae of 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFBC8390AFB0CFAB4" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1935" box="[1096,1208,1361,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ronnai">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFBC8390AFB0CFAB4" box="[1096,1208,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. ronnai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(D. Roubik, pers. comm.). I have been unable to locate these specimens to confirm this record.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="945CF93D3E3C4F0CFCC039F7FBD5F9A8" blockId="8.[807,1423,716,1903]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
A list of potential host-parasitoid records for subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFCDA3990FC40FA32" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="2004" box="[858,1012,1483,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Udamochiras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFCDA3990FC40FA32" box="[858,1012,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Udamochiras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including those newly reported in this work, is given in 
<tableCitation id="D961CC863E3C4F0CFB9D39B2FBC6FA2D" box="[1053,1138,1513,1535]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="9.[156,220,195,214]" captionText="Table 1. Potential host-parasitoid records for Melaloncha, subgenus Udamochiras spp. available in literature and from this paper. Type refers to quality of the record: records based on rearing are superior to observing attacks, which are superior to attraction to aggregations of host bees" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Table 1</tableCitation>
. Many are based only on circumstantial evidence, the result of collecting the flies attracted to aggregations of bees, often of more than one species. See individual species treatments for discussion of these records.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="945CF93D3E3C4F0DFCC03AD8FE1BFC6D" blockId="8.[807,1423,716,1903]" lastBlockId="9.[156,772,815,959]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The flies are often found either around the host nest or at flowers where bees are foraging. 
<bibRefCitation id="F07284CC3E3C4F0CFB743AFAFCEBF904" author="Simoes D &amp; Bego LR &amp; Zucchi R &amp; Sakagami SF" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="137 - 142" refId="ref31749" refString="Simoes D, Bego LR, Zucchi R, Sakagami SF. 1980. Melaloncha sinistra Borgmeier, an endoparasitic phorid fly attacking Nannotrigona (Scaptotrigona) postica Latreille (Hymenoptera, Meliponinae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologica 24: 137 - 142." type="journal article" year="1980">
Simões 
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFAD03AF9FA35F964" box="[1360,1409,1697,1719]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
., 1980
</bibRefCitation>
) noted that 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFC6D3A9AFB5DF904" authority="Borgmeier" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1971" box="[1005,1257,1728,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinistra">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFC6D3A9AFBDCF904" box="[1005,1128,1729,1750]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. sinistra</emphasis>
Borgmeier
</taxonomicName>
were found at the nest entrance of host bees but not at flowers, whereas the reverse was found for 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFB493AA5FA8EF8C1" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1935" box="[1225,1338,1790,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ronnai">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFB493AA5FA8EF8C1" box="[1225,1338,1790,1811]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. ronnai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFC063B47FBBEF8E3" authorityName="Brues" authorityYear="1904" box="[902,1034,1820,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFC063B47FBBEF8E3" box="[902,1034,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Melaloncha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been collected at the flowers of sweet potato (
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3C4F0CFC773B60FB0EF882" box="[1015,1210,1851,1872]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="batatas">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3C4F0CFC773B60FB0EF882" box="[1015,1210,1851,1872]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ipomoea batatas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.), unidentified male from Nova Teutônia, 
<collectingCountry id="ECF4B9AD3E3C4F0CFBD63B02FB2AF8BD" box="[1110,1182,1881,1903]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, in MZSP collection), caboatá (
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3D4F0DFE893F74FDE4FC97" authority="Cambess." authorityName="Cambess." box="[265,592,815,837]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Cupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vernalis">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3D4F0DFE893F74FE67FC96" box="[265,467,815,836]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Cupania vernalis</emphasis>
Cambess.
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F07284CC3E3D4F0DFDE03F74FD43FC97" author="Ronna A" box="[608,759,815,837]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="409 - 413" refId="ref31482" refString="Ronna A. 1937. Novos dados sobre os habitos de Melaloncha ronnai Borgmeier (Dipt. Phoridae), endoparasita de Apis mellifica [sic] L. Revista de Entomologia, Rio de Janeiro 7: 409 - 413." type="journal article" year="1937">Ronna, 1937</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3D4F0DFF1C3F15FEE6FCB1" box="[156,338,846,867]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Eupatorium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3D4F0DFF1C3F15FE92FCB1" box="[156,294,846,867]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Eupatorium</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3D4F0DFEE63F16FE52FCB0" box="[358,486,845,866]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
; see material examined for 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3D4F0DFF423F36FE8FFC53" authority="Brown, 2004" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2004" box="[194,315,876,898]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3D4F0DFF423F36FE8FFC53" box="[194,315,876,898]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">M. spatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BDA498543E3D4F0DFEC23F37FE2CFC53" box="[322,408,876,897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3D4F0DFE293F37FD9EFC53" box="[425,554,876,897]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Phoenix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3D4F0DFE293F37FDB7FC53" box="[425,515,876,897]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Phoenix</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
palm (B. V. Brown, pers. observ.) and 
<taxonomicName id="53E382BE3E3D4F0DFEEC3FD0FD3AFC73" authority="(Mart.)" baseAuthorityName="Mart." box="[364,654,907,929]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Syagrus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coronata">
<emphasis id="A697252F3E3D4F0DFEEC3FD0FD80FC72" box="[364,564,907,928]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Syagrus coronata</emphasis>
(Mart.)
</taxonomicName>
palms (B. V. Brown, pers. observ.).
</paragraph>
